            "ref_spans": [],
            "section": "Dear Editor,"
        },
        {
            "text": "This case suggests that hypocalcemia may occur also in Covid-19 infection. Therefore, all patients with postsurgical hypoparathyroidism should continue their treatment to avoid severe acute hypocalcemia which can be life-threatening [1] and since vitamin D deficiency, worsened by home confinement, may predispose to systemic infections [5] . Moreover, mild hypoparathyroid patients not requiring chronic treatment should undergo careful surveillance in areas characterized by the outbreak of Covid infection. Finally, since hypocalcemia may have a negative impact on cardiac outcomes [4] , we suggest calcium evaluation and monitoring in all hospitalized patients with Covid-19 infection.",
